          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, then slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> as finely as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>yellow</strong> <strong>mustard seeds</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, a splash of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl and stir until dissolved</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced cucumber </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up, then set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p><p>Tip: Give the cucumber an occasional shake while pickling</p>",
